### Use navigation icons to show direction
Directional icons should be put before or after the text to help the user understand the direction of navigation.

Use *forward* navigation icons *after* the text. For example, the chevron icon on the [call to action button](/components/button#call-to-action) shows the button will move the user forwards to the next page.

{{
    patternlibExample({"path": "components/button/examples/button-link/index.njk", "componentFolderPath": "components/button" })
}}

Use *backward* navigation icons *before* the text. For example, the chevron icon on the [back link](/components/back-link) shows the link will move the user backwards to the previous page.

{{
    patternlibExample({"path": "components/back-link/examples/back-link/index.njk", "componentFolderPath": "components/breadcrumbs" })
}}

