}}

### Icon type

To set the type of icon, use the parameter `iconType` with either of the following values:

#### Check
`"iconType": 'check'`. Use to inform user a process has been successfully completed.
{{
    patternlibExample({"path": "foundations/icons/examples/icons-list-prefix/index.njk", "componentFolderPath": "components/lists" })
}}

#### Chevron
`"iconType": 'chevron'`. Use to inform user they will move forward to the next page.
{{
    patternlibExample({"path": "components/button/examples/button-link/index.njk", "componentFolderPath": "components/button" })
}}

#### Download
`"iconType": 'download'`. Use to inform the user a file will download to their device.
{{
    patternlibExample({"path": "components/button/examples/button-download/index.njk", "componentFolderPath": "components/button" })
}}

#### Exit
`"iconType": 'exit'`. Use to inform the user they will leave the part of the service they are in.
{{
    patternlibExample({"path": "components/button/examples/button-ghost/index.njk", "componentFolderPath": "components/button" })
}}

#### Opens in a new tab
`"iconType": 'external-link'`. Use to inform the user that a new tab will open.
{{
    patternlibExample({"path": "components/button/examples/button-link-new-window/index.njk", "componentFolderPath": "components/button" })
}}

#### Lock
`"iconType": 'lock'`. Use to reassure the user their information is secure.
{{
    patternlibExample({"path": "components/panel/examples/bare/index.njk", "componentFolderPath": "components/panel" })
}}

#### Person
`"iconType": 'person'`. Use to indicate a person’s details.
{{
    patternlibExample({"path": "components/summary/examples/summary-household/index.njk", "componentFolderPath": "components/summary" })
}}

#### Print
`"iconType": 'print'`. Use to inform the user something will be sent to their printer.
{{
    patternlibExample({"path": "components/button/examples/button-print/index.njk", "componentFolderPath": "components/button" })
}}

#### Search
`"iconType": 'search'`. Use to inform the user they can search for something.

#### Social media
`"iconType": 'twitter'`, `"iconType": 'facebook'`, `"iconType": 'instagram'` or `"iconType": 'linkedin'`. Use for links to social media channels.

{{
